    <h3 class="title"><a href="/switching-popular-vote-electoral-college#comment-1917" class="active">*Median* Voter Theorem</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="http://gojomo.blogspot.com" rel="nofollow">Gordon Mohr</a> (not verified) on Tue, 2006-07-25 12:26.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Er, I meant <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Median_Voter_Theorem" rel="nofollow"><em>Median</em> Voter Theorem</a> -- and specifically that once the national vote totals become the important thing to fight over, the contestants will converge towards  a precise 50/50 split much closer than our popular vote totals of the past. (These just come close sometimes by chance, since the contestants aren't really even trying to split the national vote evenly.)</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links"><li class="first last comment_reply"><a href="/comment/reply/433/1917" class="comment_reply">reply</a></li>
