    <div class="content"><p>You seem to forget that each voter is electing their "electors", not the electors for some other State.  To suggest that the State, as an independent Sovereign, can simply ignore the expressed will of their people and subject it instead to the voters in another State is about the most undemocratic suggestion I have ever heard.</p>
